Rubidium Targets were Prepared by Sawing a 90 Degrees
Section of a Cylindrical Rb-Mn-F/3 Cristall with a
Diameter of 25 mm.

Of a Disk with a Diameter of 25 mm with a Thickness of
About 0.5 mm and a Weight of About 0.300 Gramm.
The Rb Target Used For Irradiation at 1600 MeV was an
About 2 mm Thick Pill with a Diameter of 15 mm. It was
Made by Compacting Rb/2-S-O/4 Powder.
